  "prompt": "Will data used between 2am -5am be debited from Jio data plan or is it separately taken care of?",
  "response": "For Jio users, data used between 2 AM and 5 AM is typically debited from your regular data plan, unless you have a specific plan or offer that provides additional benefits during these hours. For example, Jio has previously offered special \"Night Data\" packs or benefits where data consumed during this period is either free or comes from a separate allocation.\n\nTo confirm whether your current plan includes any such benefits, you can:\n\n1. Check your MyJio app for details of your active plan.\n2. Contact Jio customer care for clarification.\n3. Review the terms and conditions of your specific data plan.\n\nIf you don't have a special night data offer, the usage will count toward your regular data balance.",
